22 children among dead in Swiss bus crash
Twenty-eight people, including 22 children, returning from a skiing holiday, have died in a bus accident in Switzerland, a Swiss news agency reports.
The BBC reported another 24 children were injured.
The bus, registered in Belgium, was carrying 52 passengers from the cities of Lommel and Heverlee in Flanders.
It was travelling towards Sion, in the Swiss canton of Valais, and hit a wall in a motorway tunnel near the town of Sierre, on Tuesday night.